        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer250368766" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer11990609494373587922">I really wanted to like this book. I didn&apos;t like this book.<br/><br/>Things I did like:<br/><br/>* The writing. O&apos;Brien was a wordsmith. In the abstract, all of his sentences please, and some astound.<br/><br/>* Bicycle sex. I&apos;m not positive, but I&apos;m pretty sure that the narrator got it on with a bicycle. The bicycle was the aggressor.<br/><br/>* IEDs! This is before there were IEDs, mind you.<br/><br/>Things I didn&apos;t like:<br/><br/>* How horrible the book was.<br/><br/>* How long it took me to work my way through the book.<br/><br/>* The number of times I wished I was read</span>
  <span id="freeText11990609494373587922" style="display:none">I really wanted to like this book. I didn't like this book.<br /><br />Things I did like:<br /><br />* The writing. O'Brien was a wordsmith. In the abstract, all of his sentences please, and some astound.<br /><br />* Bicycle sex. I'm not positive, but I'm pretty sure that the narrator got it on with a bicycle. The bicycle was the aggressor.<br /><br />* IEDs! This is before there were IEDs, mind you.<br /><br />Things I didn't like:<br /><br />* How horrible the book was.<br /><br />* How long it took me to work my way through the book.<br /><br />* The number of times I wished I was reading a different book.<br /><br />In sum, save yourself the trouble and read Bicycle Sex: The Definitive Anthology instead. O'Brien was probably an amusing conversationalist after tweleve whiskeys, but this novel is about as amusing as the swine flu.</span>
